Hello.
I try setup bot in AWS Lambda, but bot _(Telegram)_ functions are not working.

**Example:**
```js
module.exports = async function App( context ) {
	const event = context.event;
	
	console.log(event);
	console.log(event.message.from);
	console.log(event.message.chat);

	await context.sendText( `@${event.message.from.username} - Hi!` );
```

**Lambda log:**

![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/2736539/74108065-ec430880-4b7e-11ea-9abb-2995138d0cdf.png)

In local that works well.
What could be the reason?

Hi,
In Viber I create bot. I take sample from Bottender examples and add [onConversationStarted](https://bottender.js.org/docs/APIReference-ViberEvent#code-classlanguage-textconversationstartedcode) event:
```javascript
const config = require('./bottender.config').viber;

const bot = new ViberBot({
  accessToken: config.accessToken,
});
const handler = new ViberHandler()
    .onConversationStarted(async context => {
        console.log('onConversationStarted');
    })
    .onEvent(async context => {
        console.log('onEvent');
    })
    .onError(async context => {
        console.log('Something wrong happened.');
    });
bot.onEvent(handler);

const server = createServer(bot);

const PORT = process.env.PORT || 5000;

server.listen(PORT, () => {
  console.log('server is running on 5000 port...');
});
```
In Viber docs written: ["Conversation started event fires when a user opens a conversation with the Public Account/ bot using the “message” button (found on the account’s info screen) or using a deep link."](https://developers.viber.com/docs/api/rest-bot-api/#conversation-started)
But when i using deep link or open a conversation then onConversationStarted event not fired and log not has any messages.
So, is there a way to fire onConversationStarted event?
Thanks.
